(974, 86, 'species_1_description', '<em>Mycobacterium tuberculosis</em> infects perhaps one third of the world population and causes the disease TB. In 2013 there were an estimated 450,000 cases of multi-drug resistant cases of TB, and there is an urgent need for fast and accurate diagnostics. For <em>M. tuberculosis</em>, the Mykrobe predictor identifies if the sample is from the M. tuberculosis complex (and if so, which species) or is an \"atypical mycobacterium\", and then predicts drug resistance for 3 first-line drugs (rifampicin, isoniazid, ethambutol) and also second-line drugs (streptomycin, aminoglycosides, quinolones).'),
