(1514, 100, 'species_1_description', '<em>Mycobacterium tuberculosis</em> infects perhaps one third of the world population and causes the disease TB. In 2013 there were an estimated 450,000 cases of multi-drug resistant cases of TB, and there is an urgent need for fast and accurate diagnostics.\r\n\r\nGold-standard drug resistance tests are expensive and slow, taking as long as 6-8 weeks to get results. If instead samples undergo \"liquid culture\" followed by DNA sequencing and Mykrobe predictor analysis, <em>the time to results is reduced by 4-6 weeks</em>. Results are limited by our imperfect understanding of the genetics of resistance, but this understanding is improving continually. As researchers identify mutations which cause resistance, these can rapidly be incorporated into the Mykrobe predictor and tested on thousands of samples, accelerating the transfer of research into the clinic.\r\n\r\nUnusually for DNA-based diagnostics, the Mykrobe predictor detects rare \"minor\" populations of drug resistant bacteria, which may later spread, and our analyses show this gives the Mykrobe predictor greater ability to detect drug resistance for 2nd line drugs, a critical component of dealing with multi-drug resistant TB (MDR-TB).'),
