(1908, 108, 'species_1_description', '<em>Mycobacterium tuberculosis</em> infects perhaps one third of the world population and causes the disease TB. In 2013 there were an estimated 450,000 cases of multi-drug resistant cases of TB, and there is an urgent need for fast and accurate diagnostics.\r\n\r\nGold-standard drug resistance tests are expensive and slow, taking as long as 6-8 weeks to get results. By comparison, if we use DNA-sequencing and then Mykrobe predictor analysis, <em>this can reduce the time to results by 4-6 weeks</em>.\r\n\r\nUnusually for DNA-based diagnostics, the Mykrobe predictor detects rare \"minor\" populations of drug resistant bacteria, which may later spread, and our analyses show this gives the Mykrobe predictor greater ability to detect drug resistance for 2nd line drugs, a critical component of dealing with multi-drug resistant TB (MDR-TB).'),
(1909, 108, '_species_1_description', 'field_534e153a66e4c');
